      <h2 class="f3">Helper Function Standard Components</h1>
      <p class="f5 lh-copy sans-serif">Helper functions are used to generate individual standard components e.g. a link or a button.
         They're used for a component that should consistently look the same but that may be used in multiple different contexts e.g. a styled button. </p>
      <p class="f5 lh-copy sans-serif">To use a helper standard component you need to do 3 things:</p>
      <ul class="f5 lh-copy sans-serif">
        <li>Find an existing component in <code>web/views/component_helpers</code> or create/amend your own</li>
        <li>Check your component_helper file is imported in <code>web/views/component_helpers.ex</code></li>
        <li>Call the function in your html where you wish to position the component.</li>
      </ul>
      <p class="f5 lh-copy sans-serif">Take this button for example: <%= link_primary("Click me!", to: "#somewhere") %></p>
      <p class="f5 lh-copy sans-serif">Include the following code where you want it to render:</p>
      <img src="https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/16775804/25175681/a7134716-24f3-11e7-9d8f-da1eb057c3fa.png" width= 380px/>
      <p class="f5 lh-copy sans-serif">It will call the existing function which is found in <code>web/views/component_helpers/button.ex</code>:</p>
      <img src="https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/16775804/25175893/5565244c-24f4-11e7-9dd4-a43e1a332e14.png" width= 600px/>
      <p class="f5 lh-copy sans-serif">Which you can see has been imported in <code>web/views/component_helpers.ex</code>:</p>
      <img src="https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/16775804/25179744/1226413e-2503-11e7-8b0e-52fad14d89ed.png" width= 380px/>

      <p class="f5 lh-copy sans-serif">Here are examples of our standard components that use helpers and the code used to create a new instance of them:</p>

      <h2 class="f3">Links</h2>
      <p class="measure f5 lh-copy sans-serif">Our basic anchor components.</p>

      <div class="br2 ba bw2 dark-gray b--black-10 pa3 mv4 w-40-l fl">
        <%= link_to("Link", to: coping_strategy_path(@conn, :new)) %>
      </div>
      <div class="pa3 mv4 w-60-l fl">
        <img src="https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/16775804/25176140/1bebd9d0-24f5-11e7-96b6-37c51a367d87.png" />
      </div>

      <h2 class="f3">Buttons</h1>
      <p class="measure f5 lh-copy sans-serif">Used to create a styled <code>&lt;a&gt;</code>, <code>&lt;button&gt;</code>, or <code>&lt;input&gt;</code> element.</p>

      <div class="br2 ba bw2 dark-gray b--black-10 pa3 mv4 w-50-l fl">
        <%= link_primary("Primary", to: "#somewhere") %>
        <%= link_secondary("Secondary", to: "/contact-us") %>
        <%= link_inactive("Inactive", to: "#") %>
        <%#= button("Button", to: "#", class: primary_classes) %>
      </div>
      <div class="pa3 mv4 w-50-l fl">
        <img src="https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/16775804/25179121/6a987b82-2500-11e7-8745-9769a604f595.png" />
      </div>

      <h2 class="f3 mt6 pt4">Partials Standard Components</h1>
      <p class="f5 lh-copy sans-serif">Partials are small templates.
        They are used to contain a collection of elements that are always used together.
        Partials can contain helper standard components. In the context of standard components,
         we are interested in partials that are reused and inserted in numerous places across a project.</p>
      <p class="measure f5 lh-copy sans-serif">To use a partial you need to do 3 things:</p>

      <ul class="f5 lh-copy sans-serif">
        <li>Find or create a new partial within <code>web/templates/tip/index.html.eex</code></li>
        <li>Define your partial inside your views:<code>web/views/tip_view.ex</code></li>
        <li>Create any functions needed in <code>web/views/component_view.ex</code></li>
        <li>Render the partial in your html where you wish to position it.</li>
      </ul>

    </div>
    <p class="f5 lh-copy sans-serif">Here are examples of our standard components that use partials:</p>

